ouse was the best place to come with my question since rogues are the masters of jockeying around for meele position.<br>
<br>
I started a bard on Rallos Zek. She's level 9 right now. And my skills are all maxed. But every time I get into a fight with a meele character, I get owned so bad it's not even funny. It always ends up with me getting down to two bubbles and running away while the other guy is barely scratched. And it's very annoying. I'm not expecting to dominate people. But it would be nice to at least hold my own.<br>
<br>
What happens is that they guy will be in front of me, then he's gone. I turn around, and he's not there. I turn some more and he's still not there. Then I find him for half a second and he's gone again. meanwhile he's beating me down. And I'll get a shot at him every third round or so (which I usually miss).<br>
<br>
So I've got a couple questions... since the deficiency is obviously on my part.<br>
<br>
1) When you spin around, do you use mouse look, or the arrow keys on the keyboard? Mouse look is a lot faster, but also a lot harder to control.<br>
<br>
2) What are the principles of meele pvp (aside from hit the other guy and don't get hit)? In other words... what is your objective? And does anybody have any tips on how I could improve, or things I could do to practice?<br>
<br>
Thanks.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
